OL,6,F"So, we're used to it to a point, but
OL,7,Fnot to this extreme. It's been a
OL,8,Fdifficult year and we've had wet years
OL,9,Fbefore, but the speed and the way it
OL,10,Fhappened this year is the concerning
OL,11,Fbit not just for the here and now but
OL,12,Fgoing forward from a business point of
OL,13,Fview.
OL,15,F"You can't mitigate against that.
OL,16,FThere's no insurance. You can't insure
OL,17,Fagainst any of it from a financial
OL,18,Fpoint of view."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/16
